WEBVTT

00:48.048 --> 00:50.876
[♪♪♪]

00:51.051 --> 00:52.313
[DOOR CLOSES, LOCK CLICKS]

00:52.487 --> 00:53.966
[FOOTSTEPS]

00:56.882 --> 00:58.362
[RATTLING]

01:02.018 --> 01:04.063
[KNOB RATTLING]

01:06.109 --> 01:07.328
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

01:07.502 --> 01:09.852
[YOUNG AMANDA SOBBING]

01:10.026 --> 01:13.595
YOUNG AMANDA [IN KOREAN]:

01:13.769 --> 01:15.684
[DOOR OPENS]

01:15.858 --> 01:17.990
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

01:25.737 --> 01:29.306
SOO-HYUN:

01:37.488 --> 01:42.014
UMMA [IN KOREAN]:

01:42.189 --> 01:44.104
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING]

01:44.278 --> 01:46.845
[YOUNG AMANDA SCREAMS, SOBBING]

01:55.071 --> 01:57.117
[BIRD TRILLING OUTSIDE]

02:00.598 --> 02:02.557
[CREAKING]

02:48.777 --> 02:51.127
[BABY CRYING]

03:08.710 --> 03:11.103
[♪♪♪]

04:52.988 --> 04:56.818
[♪♪♪]

04:56.992 --> 04:59.124
AMANDA:
One, two, three.

04:59.299 --> 05:00.474
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

05:02.519 --> 05:03.868
What do you wanna call her?

05:04.042 --> 05:04.869
Zizi.

05:05.043 --> 05:06.871
Zizi, okay.Mm-hm.

05:07.045 --> 05:08.264
Okay, one, two, three, Zizi.

05:08.438 --> 05:10.788
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

05:10.962 --> 05:12.921
Hi, Zizi.

05:13.095 --> 05:14.792
She's so cute.

05:21.756 --> 05:23.323
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

05:26.456 --> 05:28.371
[BUZZING]

06:04.842 --> 06:07.192
Yuck, you know
that grosses me out.

06:07.367 --> 06:09.064
What? This?

06:09.238 --> 06:10.848
Mom.[LAUGHS]

06:11.022 --> 06:12.850
Oh! Ew!

06:24.775 --> 06:25.950
No, I'm not done.

06:26.124 --> 06:27.561
You're such a slow reader.

06:29.737 --> 06:31.608
Did you get to the part where--?Shh.

06:37.571 --> 06:39.050
[SUCKS TEETH][CHUCKLES]

06:43.881 --> 06:45.187
Mmm...

06:55.632 --> 06:57.852
[THUNDER CRASHING]

07:50.426 --> 07:53.603
[THUNDER CRASHING][AMANDA GASPING]

08:00.436 --> 08:03.004
[AMANDA SOBS, SNIFFLES]

08:06.355 --> 08:07.748
Mom?

08:17.758 --> 08:18.759
[THUNDER CRASHES][GASPING]

08:30.205 --> 08:32.554
[CRYING SOFTLY,
SNIFFLING]

08:32.729 --> 08:33.948
Hey.

08:35.602 --> 08:37.255
[MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY]

08:42.957 --> 08:43.523
[INHALES SHARPLY]

08:45.002 --> 08:46.656
The lightning is too far away.

08:46.830 --> 08:48.005
It can't hurt you.

08:53.184 --> 08:55.447
[HUMMING TUNE]

09:17.426 --> 09:19.471
[ROOSTER CROWING]

09:25.913 --> 09:28.437
ANNOUNCER [ON RADIO]:
Second down nine,
from their own 35.

09:28.611 --> 09:31.788
[♪♪♪]

09:31.962 --> 09:33.137
The score--[RADIO SHUTS OFF]

09:54.463 --> 09:55.333
BOTH:
Boo!

09:55.507 --> 09:56.596
[BOTH LAUGH]

09:58.554 --> 10:00.991
Hey, here's for
your fluffy little friends.

10:01.165 --> 10:02.471
Sweet.

10:04.168 --> 10:06.257
AMANDA:
Here are our
last quarter's statements.

10:06.431 --> 10:08.259
Wait till you see
this quarter.

10:08.433 --> 10:11.219
Remember how I've been trying
to sell your honey online?

10:11.393 --> 10:13.264
Remember how I thought
it was a waste of time?

10:13.438 --> 10:17.965
Vividly. But maybe it wasn't
such a waste of time after all.

10:18.139 --> 10:21.272
Can barely keep up with orders.
Keep selling out.

10:21.446 --> 10:23.405
But... How?

10:25.363 --> 10:26.887
Apparently
some lifestyle influencer

10:27.061 --> 10:28.715
posted about your honey,

10:28.889 --> 10:30.542
and it kind of went viral.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.196
I don't know
what any of that means.

10:32.370 --> 10:35.069
To be honest, Amanda,
I don't think I do either.

10:35.243 --> 10:38.638
My niece tried
to explain it to me, but...

10:38.812 --> 10:43.207
What I do know is I can sell
every drop of this you make.

10:43.381 --> 10:44.165
And more.

10:54.741 --> 10:55.916
[CHUCKLES][LAUGHS]

10:56.090 --> 10:58.048
Hey, want some juice?Oh, yes, please.

11:06.622 --> 11:07.362
What is this?

11:08.624 --> 11:10.147
We need more colonies.

11:10.321 --> 11:13.629
Danny says our honey keeps
selling out on the Internet.

11:13.803 --> 11:15.239
But that's a lot more work.

11:15.413 --> 11:18.329
Yeah, but this is
what we do, right?

11:18.503 --> 11:20.288
It's nothing the two of us
can't handle together.

11:20.462 --> 11:21.681
Thank you.

11:24.031 --> 11:26.120
Actually, Mom,
I was thinking maybe--

11:26.294 --> 11:28.426
Take that to Danny
after breakfast, would you?

11:28.600 --> 11:31.168
[♪♪♪]

11:53.582 --> 11:54.975
[HORN HONKS]

11:56.237 --> 11:57.455
[HONKING]

11:57.629 --> 11:59.327
Excuse me. Hello.

11:59.501 --> 12:01.024
[SPEAKS IN KOREAN]

12:02.591 --> 12:03.548
Excuse me?

12:03.723 --> 12:05.376
[MUTTERING IN KOREAN]

12:08.510 --> 12:09.859
I don't understand you.

12:11.556 --> 12:14.081
[IN ENGLISH]
Oh. Thank you. Thank you.

12:49.638 --> 12:50.813
Stop.

12:52.554 --> 12:53.860
Stop. Don't come any closer.

12:57.864 --> 12:59.604
Shut the car off. Turn it off.

13:00.867 --> 13:02.651
[IN KOREAN]

13:04.479 --> 13:05.088
Who are you?

13:10.441 --> 13:11.399
[IN KOREAN]

13:40.776 --> 13:42.822
[♪♪♪]

14:33.698 --> 14:35.526
[TUTS]

14:35.700 --> 14:36.919
[SIGHS]

14:37.093 --> 14:38.573
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS]

15:05.905 --> 15:08.646
[♪♪♪]

15:12.476 --> 15:14.087
[SLURPS]

15:14.261 --> 15:15.218
[SIGHS]

15:58.609 --> 16:01.656
UMMA [IN KOREAN]:

16:01.830 --> 16:04.398
KANG:

16:56.363 --> 16:58.539
[IN ENGLISH]
Get out of my house.

16:58.713 --> 17:00.497
[SIGHS]

17:13.380 --> 17:14.858
[DOOR CLOSES]

17:27.959 --> 17:29.396
BOY:
There she is.

17:29.570 --> 17:31.702
[ALL CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY,
LAUGHING]

17:37.056 --> 17:38.144
Hey, Danny.

17:38.318 --> 17:40.798
Hey, I was
just thinking about you.

17:40.972 --> 17:43.497
Come here. There's a waiting
list to buy your honey.

17:46.021 --> 17:47.457
Cool, right?
Yeah.

17:47.631 --> 17:49.329
Cool.

17:51.722 --> 17:52.767
Okay.

17:54.116 --> 17:56.597
She building more hives?

17:56.771 --> 17:59.208
Great. I may have to order
some of this stuff.

17:59.382 --> 18:01.254
Let me check stock
and see what we have.

18:01.428 --> 18:03.299
River, will you watch
the counter for a second?

18:03.473 --> 18:06.563
Why? You think
she's gonna rob the place?

18:06.737 --> 18:08.609
DANNY:
This is my niece,

18:08.783 --> 18:10.480
who will be staying with me
a few weeks

18:10.654 --> 18:12.308
while her folks are out of town.

18:12.482 --> 18:14.223
River, this is Chris.Hey.

18:15.616 --> 18:16.704
Hey.

18:21.665 --> 18:22.492
I like your makeup.

18:24.755 --> 18:26.105
Thanks.

18:26.279 --> 18:27.671
I really like your freckles.

18:27.845 --> 18:29.238
Wish I had them.

18:29.412 --> 18:31.197
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

18:35.288 --> 18:38.160
[♪♪♪]

18:58.049 --> 18:59.964
[CLATTERING]

19:08.669 --> 19:11.237
[♪♪♪]

19:40.527 --> 19:42.181
[DOOR OPENS]CHRIS: Mom?

19:57.239 --> 19:58.501
No. Don't touch that.

19:58.675 --> 20:00.024
Why?

20:00.199 --> 20:01.200
Where'd it come from?

20:02.897 --> 20:04.333
Wait.

20:04.507 --> 20:05.943
Was someone here earlier?

20:07.989 --> 20:09.208
What's on your face?

20:11.210 --> 20:14.082
[AMANDA WALKS UP STAIRS]

20:55.254 --> 20:57.734
[♪♪♪]

21:29.157 --> 21:30.550
[GROANS][GASPS]

21:39.994 --> 21:40.777
[LATCHES CLICK]

22:01.058 --> 22:02.973
[WINDOW RATTLES][GASPS]

22:06.803 --> 22:08.152
[DOOR SLAMS]

22:16.813 --> 22:17.597
Chris?

22:24.865 --> 22:26.519
[RATTLING]

22:32.525 --> 22:34.004
CHRIS [SCREAMS]:
Mommy!

22:35.397 --> 22:36.703
Chrissy?

22:38.531 --> 22:40.141
I'm coming.

22:43.405 --> 22:45.276
Chris, I'm coming.

22:45.451 --> 22:46.365
CHRIS:
Mom?

22:46.539 --> 22:49.106
Chrissy.[CHRIS SCREAMS]

22:49.280 --> 22:50.978
Chrissy.[CHRIS SOBBING]

22:52.675 --> 22:54.285
Chrissy, where are you?

22:56.070 --> 22:57.898
Mommy!Oh, God.

22:58.072 --> 23:01.031
Honey, answer me.[CHRIS SOBBING]

23:01.205 --> 23:02.424
Mommy!

23:02.598 --> 23:03.643
[CHRIS SCREAMS]

23:03.817 --> 23:05.558
Chris?Help!

23:07.168 --> 23:09.039
[SOBBING, SCREAMING STOP]

23:11.477 --> 23:14.349
[MUSIC BOX PLAYING TUNE]

23:23.532 --> 23:24.446
UMMA [SOFTLY, IN KOREAN]:

23:36.023 --> 23:36.589
[GASPS]

23:49.036 --> 23:50.559
[CHICK CHIRPING]

24:00.439 --> 24:02.310
Come here.

24:02.484 --> 24:04.355
[SCREAMS]Soo-Hyun.

24:04.530 --> 24:06.183
[GASPING]

24:06.357 --> 24:08.403
Mom.
[PANTING]

24:08.577 --> 24:10.666
Were you having a nightmare?

24:13.452 --> 24:15.062
[SOFTLY]
Yeah.

24:18.892 --> 24:21.068
[♪♪♪]

24:26.987 --> 24:28.597
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

24:28.771 --> 24:30.338
[CLUCKING]

24:34.560 --> 24:35.517
[DOOR OPENS]

24:40.653 --> 24:41.567
Hey.

24:41.741 --> 24:43.307
Are you okay?

24:46.528 --> 24:47.877
You're just acting
kind of weird.

24:52.534 --> 24:54.144
Where did this come from?

24:57.583 --> 25:00.368
Chrissy, I asked you a question.

25:00.542 --> 25:01.717
It was Danny.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.199
He gave it to me.

25:05.373 --> 25:06.940
Danny? Why?

25:07.114 --> 25:09.159
Because he's my friend.

25:09.333 --> 25:11.074
He's not your friend.
I do his books.

25:11.248 --> 25:13.207
I pay him to help us.

25:13.381 --> 25:15.209
He's your friend too, Mom.

25:16.515 --> 25:19.343
He's our only friend.

25:23.478 --> 25:24.914
So you wanna go to college?

25:25.088 --> 25:26.133
No.

25:26.307 --> 25:27.264
No?

25:33.314 --> 25:35.185
[BUZZING]

25:47.458 --> 25:49.765
[YOUNG AMANDA CRYING, ECHOING]

25:55.641 --> 25:57.338
[YOUNG AMANDA SOBBING,
SPEAKING IN KOREAN]

25:57.512 --> 26:00.080
[DOOR RATTLING]

26:00.254 --> 26:02.082
[UMMA SPEAKING IN KOREAN]

26:02.256 --> 26:06.521
[DOOR CONTINUES RATTLING] [YOUNG AMANDA WAILING]

26:06.695 --> 26:09.480
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING] [YOUNG AMANDA SCREAMING]

26:09.655 --> 26:11.352
[BUZZING INTENSIFIES,
GLASS RATTLING]

26:11.526 --> 26:13.963
Oh, nice haul.

26:14.137 --> 26:16.618
That'll make some
of your customers real happy.

26:19.316 --> 26:20.709
Wha...?

26:20.883 --> 26:22.755
What's up?
Did I say something wrong?

26:24.670 --> 26:26.541
Uh, you know,

26:26.715 --> 26:28.761
I never, in a million years,

26:28.935 --> 26:30.632
thought I would be a beekeeper.

26:30.806 --> 26:33.200
I mean, I'm--
I'm an accountant.

26:33.374 --> 26:35.506
What did I know
about making honey?

26:35.681 --> 26:37.726
But more than that,

26:37.900 --> 26:39.989
I hated bees.

26:40.163 --> 26:42.644
I hated the sound they made.

26:42.818 --> 26:47.954
The constant buzzing that
just crawls under your skin.

26:48.128 --> 26:49.738
But then one day,

26:49.912 --> 26:53.263
Chrissy came home
with a book about beekeeping

26:53.437 --> 26:56.005
and became obsessed
with the idea.

26:56.179 --> 26:58.921
She wanted
to start a hive so badly.

26:59.095 --> 27:00.749
She even asked me
to help her convince you.

27:04.318 --> 27:06.494
I was nervous at first, but...

27:08.061 --> 27:09.889
Chrissy...

27:10.063 --> 27:11.368
was fearless.

27:11.542 --> 27:14.154
Yeah.Surrounded by all those bees.

27:14.328 --> 27:16.025
But it made her so happy.

27:16.199 --> 27:17.853
And that made me happy.

27:18.027 --> 27:21.335
It made me feel
like I was a good mother.

27:21.509 --> 27:24.904
So we kept adding more hives.

27:25.078 --> 27:27.820
It was something we were
always supposed to do together.

27:29.778 --> 27:32.563
So I was really surprised

27:32.738 --> 27:37.090
when I found the college
application that you gave her.

27:37.264 --> 27:39.353
Oh, look, I-I gave her
that application,

27:39.527 --> 27:42.835
but that's because
she asked me for it.

27:43.009 --> 27:47.013
You probably think
this is not any of my business,

27:47.187 --> 27:49.668
but don't you think going to
college could be good for her?

27:49.842 --> 27:51.626
You know, make some friends,

27:51.800 --> 27:54.455
learn to live life
on her own a little?

27:58.981 --> 28:01.114
I'm sorry.
You didn't really expect

28:01.288 --> 28:03.594
she was gonna
stay here forever, did you?

28:03.769 --> 28:06.685
[♪♪♪]

28:08.991 --> 28:10.906
[TICKING]

28:27.706 --> 28:29.620
YOUNG AMANDA [IN ENGLISH]:
No. No.

28:29.795 --> 28:31.710
UMMA:

28:35.539 --> 28:38.020
YOUNG AMANDA:
I hate you.
I wish you were dead.

28:38.194 --> 28:41.415
UMMA:

28:59.999 --> 29:02.218
[♪♪♪]

29:13.534 --> 29:16.972
[♪♪♪]

29:48.090 --> 29:50.223
[EXHALES SHARPLY]DANNY: You didn't really expect

29:50.397 --> 29:53.574
that she was gonna
stay here forever, did you?

29:53.748 --> 29:55.924
[♪♪♪]

30:17.641 --> 30:19.382
[RUSTLING]

30:51.850 --> 30:54.243
[♪♪♪]

31:04.819 --> 31:07.691
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

31:26.319 --> 31:26.928
[GASPS]

31:51.822 --> 31:52.736
[SOFTLY]
Chris.

32:10.667 --> 32:11.277
Chris?

32:27.902 --> 32:29.686
[BEES BUZZING]

32:54.102 --> 32:55.669
UMMA:

32:55.843 --> 32:58.237
[HEART BEATING]

33:32.271 --> 33:33.489
[GASPING]

33:41.671 --> 33:42.237
Chrissy?

33:45.545 --> 33:46.850
Why are you wearing that?

33:47.025 --> 33:48.548
I'm sorry, Mommy.
I was just trying it on.

33:48.722 --> 33:50.202
I found it up here.

33:51.551 --> 33:52.813
Take it off.Why?

33:52.987 --> 33:53.683
Take it off.
Why?

33:56.991 --> 33:58.688
[DESCENDING STAIRS]

34:18.882 --> 34:20.188
[ELECTRICITY BUZZING][YOUNG AMANDA SCREAMS]

34:33.940 --> 34:34.507
[SIGHS]

34:51.350 --> 34:52.177
What's going on?

34:57.617 --> 34:59.184
You've been acting...

35:01.186 --> 35:03.449
I'm just worried about you.

35:03.623 --> 35:04.972
[SOFTLY]
I'm fine.

35:10.499 --> 35:11.631
What's in the suitcase?

35:11.805 --> 35:13.502
[SLAPS TABLE]I said, I'm fine.

35:19.595 --> 35:22.903
[♪♪♪]

35:39.006 --> 35:41.400
[HEART BEATING]

36:11.081 --> 36:13.649
[♪♪♪]

36:50.991 --> 36:52.601
[ROPE CREAKING]

37:29.638 --> 37:30.726
[GASPS]

37:38.604 --> 37:42.521
[HEART BEATING]

38:16.990 --> 38:18.731
[DEEP VOICE]
Disobedient little girl.

38:20.123 --> 38:20.776
[GASPS]

38:25.955 --> 38:26.956
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

38:49.544 --> 38:50.502
[GASPS]

38:54.157 --> 38:55.463
[SCREAMS]

38:57.030 --> 38:58.814
[POUNDING]YOUNG AMANDA: Mom.

38:58.988 --> 39:00.076
Let me out, please.

39:00.250 --> 39:01.382
[IN KOREAN]

39:03.253 --> 39:04.472
[POUNDING]

39:12.350 --> 39:14.482
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

39:14.656 --> 39:16.528
[KNOCKING]

39:16.702 --> 39:18.051
CHRIS:
Mommy, let me out.

39:18.225 --> 39:20.227
Chris?Mommy?

39:20.401 --> 39:21.228
Chris?

39:21.402 --> 39:23.099
It's too heavy.[GRUNTS]

39:23.273 --> 39:25.363
Chrissy.[SHUDDERING]

39:25.537 --> 39:27.147
What were you doing down there?

39:29.279 --> 39:30.411
Are you okay?

39:35.198 --> 39:36.461
Who is this woman?

39:38.245 --> 39:39.725
Tell me who she is.

39:44.599 --> 39:45.426
Fine.

39:46.819 --> 39:49.343
Don't talk to me.

39:49.517 --> 39:51.171
But when I'm gone,
you'll have no one left

39:51.345 --> 39:52.564
to keep your secrets from.

39:54.914 --> 39:56.437
Chris.

39:56.611 --> 39:59.527
Someone did come
to our house the other day.

39:59.701 --> 40:01.355
With a suitcase.

40:02.965 --> 40:04.924
That man was my uncle.

40:05.098 --> 40:09.145
He came here from Korea
to tell me my mother died.

40:09.319 --> 40:13.193
Grandma Gloria and Grandpa Bill
aren't my real parents.

40:13.367 --> 40:14.455
I made them up.

40:15.848 --> 40:17.458
I was raised by my mother.

40:19.808 --> 40:20.983
My real mother.

40:22.594 --> 40:24.509
CHRIS:
What's inside?

40:24.683 --> 40:26.772
My mother's remains.

40:26.946 --> 40:29.296
And her most
cherished possessions.

40:31.341 --> 40:32.081
[LATCHES CLICK]

40:32.255 --> 40:35.128
[♪♪♪]

40:48.968 --> 40:49.969
Is this her?

40:51.144 --> 40:53.146
Your mom?

40:53.320 --> 40:54.364
[SOFTLY]
That's my umma.

40:56.279 --> 40:57.150
Umma.

40:59.239 --> 41:02.068
I never thought I'd be
in the same room with her again.

41:05.027 --> 41:06.942
What else have you been lying
to me about?

41:07.116 --> 41:08.944
No, Chrissy, I...

41:12.165 --> 41:13.514
What do you wanna know?

41:15.516 --> 41:16.735
Was this hers?

41:19.389 --> 41:21.174
It's called a hanbok.

41:21.348 --> 41:22.654
She made it herself.

41:25.004 --> 41:27.136
She was very proud of her work.

41:27.310 --> 41:28.964
She hoped
to pass it down to me.

41:36.711 --> 41:37.712
What's this?

41:39.322 --> 41:40.541
That's a tal.

41:40.715 --> 41:43.936
It's a family heirloom.

41:44.110 --> 41:48.201
It's been worn by the women
in our family for generations.

41:48.375 --> 41:50.420
Why is all this stuff in here?

41:50.595 --> 41:51.900
She always said she'd take

41:52.074 --> 41:54.033
her favorite things
with her to the afterlife.

41:54.207 --> 41:56.514
She probably left them
for her ceremony.

41:56.688 --> 41:58.951
What kind of ceremony?

41:59.125 --> 42:01.431
Well, some Koreans believe
that life's hardships

42:01.606 --> 42:04.783
are caused by the tormented
spirits of their ancestors,

42:04.957 --> 42:08.177
so they make offerings
to appease their tortured souls.

42:09.831 --> 42:10.745
Is that what you believe?

42:13.182 --> 42:14.749
I don't believe in superstition.

42:25.368 --> 42:27.327
There's something else
in here.

42:31.505 --> 42:33.725
[♪♪♪]

42:46.520 --> 42:47.695
What is it?

42:50.698 --> 42:52.091
[YOUNG AMANDA SOBBING]

42:52.265 --> 42:53.266
Mom?

43:09.804 --> 43:10.718
What's wrong?

43:16.376 --> 43:18.639
[♪♪♪]

43:23.383 --> 43:25.428
UMMA:

43:25.603 --> 43:26.865
[YOUNG AMANDA CRYING]

43:31.086 --> 43:33.088
YOUNG AMANDA [IN KOREAN]:

43:33.915 --> 43:37.223
UMMA:

43:45.144 --> 43:46.275
Good morning.[CHICKENS CLUCKING]

43:49.235 --> 43:50.453
[NOISE IN DISTANCE]

43:50.628 --> 43:52.804
[♪♪♪]

44:09.385 --> 44:10.778
Hey.
Hi.

44:10.952 --> 44:13.215
Oh, here.No, no, hey, I got it.

44:13.389 --> 44:14.739
It's what you pay me for.

44:16.610 --> 44:19.613
Um, is your niece still here?

44:19.787 --> 44:22.050
I was thinking about
having a game night with Chris,

44:22.224 --> 44:23.922
if you guys wanted to join.

44:24.096 --> 44:25.880
I thought it would be
good for her.

44:27.360 --> 44:28.709
Great.

44:39.415 --> 44:41.243
[SIGHS SOFTLY]

44:45.944 --> 44:47.815
Do you want me to do your hair?

44:50.775 --> 44:52.254
[AMANDA HUMMING TUNE]

45:01.394 --> 45:04.179
[♪♪♪]

45:04.353 --> 45:07.574
[SQUELCHING]

45:09.489 --> 45:11.317
Ow!

45:11.491 --> 45:12.840
Not so hard.

45:13.014 --> 45:13.972
[WHISPERS]
Sorry.

45:15.756 --> 45:17.627
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

45:19.151 --> 45:21.240
Oh!

45:21.414 --> 45:22.589
[DANNY CHUCKLES]

45:24.896 --> 45:26.854
Sorry.[CHUCKLES]

45:27.028 --> 45:30.292
AMANDA:
Ten. Yellow ten. Yellow ten,
yellow ten, yellow ten.

45:30.466 --> 45:32.599
Isn't there like a time limit
on each hand?

45:32.773 --> 45:34.296
[SNICKERS]
Oh, oh, oh.

45:34.470 --> 45:36.298
I think I got it. Uh...
Uh-huh.

45:36.472 --> 45:38.736
Ah-ah, Rummikub.

45:38.910 --> 45:39.998
DANNY: Rummikub.AMANDA: Yeah...

45:40.172 --> 45:41.434
Do you wanna go
hang out upstairs?

45:41.608 --> 45:42.565
DANNY:
Is it?

45:42.740 --> 45:44.219
Yes.AMANDA: Really?

45:44.393 --> 45:46.308
You don't wanna play
another round?

45:46.482 --> 45:48.310
No. No, it's okay.

45:48.484 --> 45:49.747
Thank you.

45:50.791 --> 45:51.879
Okay.

45:57.102 --> 45:58.364
Cool spot.

46:00.932 --> 46:02.237
Is that a college application?

46:02.411 --> 46:04.152
Yeah.

46:04.326 --> 46:06.502
I didn't even know
you could apply on paper.

46:09.854 --> 46:12.073
Your life is so retro.

46:12.247 --> 46:14.162
Do you even have a phone?

46:14.336 --> 46:16.034
No.

46:16.208 --> 46:18.601
So how do you talk
to your friends?

46:18.776 --> 46:20.255
Well, my mom is my friend.

46:22.997 --> 46:25.957
But I totally have
other friends.

46:26.131 --> 46:27.001
[CHUCKLES]

46:28.873 --> 46:32.180
So you pinch the X
in the middle,

46:32.354 --> 46:34.922
then you go under to go over,
and then pull it out.

46:35.096 --> 46:37.316
Nice. Take it out.

46:37.490 --> 46:38.839
Good job.
[CHUCKLES]

46:39.013 --> 46:40.232
Like this.

46:40.406 --> 46:42.408
Pinch this. Then this.

46:42.582 --> 46:45.672
I talked about you with those
kids that hang out at the store.

46:48.240 --> 46:49.458
You what?

46:49.632 --> 46:50.851
Just think it's so funny.

46:52.461 --> 46:54.115
I mean, how lame can you get?

46:54.289 --> 46:56.248
They literally have
nothing better to do

46:56.422 --> 46:59.164
than gossip about
why you live like this.

46:59.338 --> 47:00.252
It's pathetic.

47:03.472 --> 47:04.865
[CELL PHONE BUZZING]

47:07.215 --> 47:09.261
[PHONE CLICKS ON]Is that your phone?

47:09.435 --> 47:11.263
Yeah.

47:13.743 --> 47:15.615
Danny didn't tell you
to leave it in the car?

47:15.789 --> 47:18.096
He did, but--You have to turn it off.

47:18.270 --> 47:20.359
My mom can't be
near electricity.

47:20.533 --> 47:21.664
What? Why not?

47:21.839 --> 47:24.189
She'll get really sick.

47:24.363 --> 47:26.191
Okay. Um...

47:26.365 --> 47:28.454
I had my phone with me
this whole time,

47:28.628 --> 47:29.934
and your mom seemed fine.

47:30.108 --> 47:33.111
What happens
when she gets sick?

47:43.121 --> 47:45.775
Shit, I haven't
had a beer since...

47:45.950 --> 47:47.342
Since before Chris.

47:49.388 --> 47:51.564
Really?[CHUCKLES] It's not like...

47:51.738 --> 47:54.175
You know, it's not like
Chris can be my drinking buddy.

47:54.349 --> 47:55.916
[CHUCKLES]

47:56.090 --> 47:57.613
[KNEE CRACKING]

47:57.787 --> 48:00.181
Whoa. Is that you?

48:00.355 --> 48:02.183
Yeah, my damn knee has
been killing me lately.

48:02.357 --> 48:05.012
Mm.
Oh, God.

48:05.186 --> 48:07.406
I can hear myself
turning into my mother.

48:09.930 --> 48:12.802
[♪♪♪]

48:15.544 --> 48:17.633
[THUNDER RUMBLING IN DISTANCE]

48:17.807 --> 48:20.506
[HEART BEATING]

48:20.680 --> 48:23.596
UMMA:

48:25.250 --> 48:27.078
Amanda, you okay?

48:28.688 --> 48:30.037
I think...

48:36.261 --> 48:39.264
[WHISPERS]
I think there's
something wrong.

48:39.438 --> 48:41.614
Chris is such a good kid,
you know.

48:41.788 --> 48:43.616
Just talk to her.

49:21.697 --> 49:23.656
I didn't want you to know her.

49:26.485 --> 49:29.618
My father said
she was so radiant,

49:29.792 --> 49:32.012
and so fun,

49:32.186 --> 49:35.102
when they first got married
in Korea.

49:35.276 --> 49:38.149
And then they came to America.

49:38.323 --> 49:40.020
The land of the...
The free.

49:42.153 --> 49:43.893
The land of opportunities.

49:46.157 --> 49:48.768
I think we were happy.

49:48.942 --> 49:51.379
He was completely enamored
with this place.

49:53.033 --> 49:54.469
But my mom...

49:57.690 --> 49:59.126
she struggled.

50:02.129 --> 50:05.654
Everything here
felt foreign to her.

50:07.004 --> 50:09.919
She was scared all the time.

50:10.094 --> 50:11.399
She stopped leaving the house.

50:11.573 --> 50:13.097
She changed.

50:13.271 --> 50:17.405
I remember so much screaming.

50:17.579 --> 50:20.321
I think my dad
couldn't take it anymore.

50:20.495 --> 50:23.237
And after he left,
I was all she had.

50:24.804 --> 50:26.240
So I had to do it all.

50:30.027 --> 50:31.550
I had to take it all.

50:34.248 --> 50:35.728
All her rage.

50:37.643 --> 50:38.905
Her spite.

50:40.863 --> 50:41.951
And her...

50:42.126 --> 50:44.780
[YOUNG AMANDA SOBBING]

50:44.954 --> 50:47.522
[♪♪♪]

50:55.965 --> 50:59.926
The moment I got pregnant,
I made myself a promise.

51:00.100 --> 51:01.406
I made you a promise.

51:03.712 --> 51:06.280
I will never become my mother.

51:33.742 --> 51:37.311
[HEART BEATING]

51:40.532 --> 51:42.099
UMMA:

51:49.193 --> 51:52.109
[♪♪♪]

52:11.998 --> 52:14.566
[HEART BEATING]

52:22.008 --> 52:26.230
UMMA:

52:32.932 --> 52:34.629
[HEART BEATING RAPIDLY]

52:41.549 --> 52:43.638
[SCREAMS]

52:49.775 --> 52:52.169
[CONTINUES STRIKING PIANO KEYS]

53:23.635 --> 53:24.940
[GRUNTS][BEES BUZZING]

53:28.509 --> 53:31.338
[♪♪♪]

53:50.531 --> 53:52.794
Why would you do this?

53:52.968 --> 53:53.839
Do what?

53:54.013 --> 53:55.319
This.

53:56.624 --> 53:58.365
It's ruined.

53:58.539 --> 54:00.802
I'll have to do it again.

54:00.976 --> 54:02.369
I didn't do that.

54:02.543 --> 54:04.806
Well, if you didn't do it,
then who did?

54:04.980 --> 54:07.592
[♪♪♪]

54:14.512 --> 54:15.382
Mom.

54:23.085 --> 54:25.000
She's here.

54:25.174 --> 54:26.828
What?She's the one

54:27.002 --> 54:29.788
who did this
to your application.

54:29.962 --> 54:30.702
Who?

54:33.400 --> 54:34.706
[WHISPERS]
Umma.

54:34.880 --> 54:37.404
She thinks
you're running away from us.

54:37.578 --> 54:39.014
There's no point
in talking to you

54:39.188 --> 54:40.755
if you're gonna act like this.

54:40.929 --> 54:42.627
Act like what?

54:42.801 --> 54:44.498
Like a psycho bitch.

54:50.287 --> 54:52.201
Hey.

54:52.376 --> 54:54.334
What did you call me?

54:54.508 --> 54:56.945
I called you a crazy psycho.

54:57.119 --> 54:58.164
And you know what?

54:58.338 --> 54:59.731
I can't wait to leave.

54:59.905 --> 55:01.646
Leave?

55:01.820 --> 55:04.213
Oh, honey,
you're not going anywhere.

55:04.388 --> 55:06.912
You can't force me to stay.

55:07.086 --> 55:08.566
I don't have to.

55:08.740 --> 55:10.568
Sweetie, sweetie.

55:12.221 --> 55:14.441
You can't even make friends.

55:14.615 --> 55:16.617
You're too scared.

55:16.791 --> 55:19.446
I'm the one who had to invite
River to game night for you.

55:19.620 --> 55:21.492
Why are you acting like this?

55:24.973 --> 55:26.801
I'm your mother.

55:26.975 --> 55:29.413
I'm the only one
who is gonna tell you the truth.

55:30.588 --> 55:32.677
And the truth is...

55:32.851 --> 55:34.418
you can't do it.

55:38.683 --> 55:41.599
Fine, leave.
Are you forgetting what happened

55:41.773 --> 55:43.557
the last time
you tried to go to school?

55:43.731 --> 55:45.907
The time before that?
Or the time before that?

55:46.081 --> 55:49.084
Are you forgetting how
you'd run home crying every day?

55:49.258 --> 55:51.435
"Mommy, nobody wants
to play with me.

55:51.609 --> 55:53.132
Mommy, they call me names."Shut up.

55:53.306 --> 55:55.352
You begged me
to homeschool you, didn't you?

55:55.526 --> 55:57.658
You pleaded with me.

55:57.832 --> 56:00.313
So, what did I do?
I homeschooled you.

56:00.487 --> 56:02.707
You wanted friends?
I was your friend.

56:02.881 --> 56:04.709
You wanted
to build a bee colony?

56:04.883 --> 56:06.754
I built you one
with my own hands.

56:06.928 --> 56:08.843
Everything I have done
since the day you were born

56:09.017 --> 56:10.628
has been for you.
To make you happy.

56:10.802 --> 56:11.890
To give you a home.

56:12.064 --> 56:14.022
A good home. A safe home.

56:14.196 --> 56:16.721
All of this is for you.

56:16.895 --> 56:18.549
You think
all of this is for me?

56:20.377 --> 56:22.335
Do you mean living like this?

56:22.509 --> 56:25.599
Cut off from the rest of
the world, like total freaks?

56:25.773 --> 56:28.689
You're delusional.
You're just hiding something.

56:28.863 --> 56:32.040
It doesn't really hurt you,
does it?

56:32.214 --> 56:34.347
The electricity.

56:34.521 --> 56:36.262
What?

56:36.436 --> 56:37.655
Your sickness.

56:37.829 --> 56:40.005
It's not real.

56:40.179 --> 56:42.224
Yes, it is.

56:42.399 --> 56:44.662
Just because you can't see it--It's not.

56:46.925 --> 56:48.405
It's just a made-up thing.

56:48.579 --> 56:52.365
Some demented,
imaginary thing in your head.

56:52.539 --> 56:54.019
And it's fucking pathetic.

57:02.331 --> 57:04.943
You said you'd never
become your mother.

57:05.117 --> 57:06.640
But that's just another lie.

57:09.948 --> 57:11.079
Chris.

57:11.253 --> 57:12.820
Chris, where are you going?

57:13.995 --> 57:15.127
Chris?

57:16.433 --> 57:18.565
Chris, don't leave.

57:18.739 --> 57:19.740
Chris.

57:19.914 --> 57:20.480
Oh.

57:23.657 --> 57:24.832
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

57:29.924 --> 57:30.838
DANNY:
Chris.

57:31.012 --> 57:32.361
Did you know it wasn't real?

57:32.536 --> 57:33.972
Her sickness?

57:34.146 --> 57:35.626
The electricity?

57:37.236 --> 57:38.585
Did you know?

57:41.327 --> 57:42.633
It's real to her.

57:45.592 --> 57:47.115
Why didn't you say anything?

57:47.289 --> 57:49.814
I did. I tried so many times
to get her to see someone.

57:49.988 --> 57:51.990
But she refused to go.
She kept insisting--

57:52.164 --> 57:54.601
No, why didn't you
say anything to me?

57:54.775 --> 57:55.820
I don't...

57:57.735 --> 57:59.388
I don't know.
I thought you knew.

57:59.563 --> 58:02.479
Of course I didn't know.

58:02.653 --> 58:05.743
If I knew, I would have
done something about it.

58:05.917 --> 58:07.527
Wait, let me drive you home.

58:13.011 --> 58:15.535
[♪♪♪]

58:29.984 --> 58:31.246
Is this what you want?

58:31.420 --> 58:33.205
A final resting place?

58:45.522 --> 58:47.393
Now leave me alone.

59:13.201 --> 59:15.464
UMMA:

59:17.989 --> 59:19.207
[SCREAMING]

59:32.569 --> 59:34.483
[GRUNTS]
Let me go!

59:34.658 --> 59:37.835
[GASPING, COUGHS]

59:44.058 --> 59:46.844
[♪♪♪]

01:00:00.640 --> 01:00:01.728
[SCREAMS]

01:00:08.256 --> 01:00:09.475
[GASPING]

01:00:11.782 --> 01:00:13.000
[BODY THUDS]

01:00:15.089 --> 01:00:16.961
[RUSTLING]

01:00:24.533 --> 01:00:25.404
[HORN HONKING]

01:00:25.578 --> 01:00:26.666
Go away.

01:00:38.504 --> 01:00:39.723
Want a ride?

01:00:46.947 --> 01:00:48.949
I got you something.

01:00:49.123 --> 01:00:51.212
It's a little
going-away present.

01:00:51.386 --> 01:00:53.345
Well, technically
I'm the one leaving,

01:00:53.519 --> 01:00:55.913
so I guess just a present,
but anyway...

01:00:56.087 --> 01:00:57.044
What is this?

01:00:57.218 --> 01:00:59.264
It's a planner for school.

01:00:59.438 --> 01:01:04.182
You can put your class
assignments in it, schedule...

01:01:04.356 --> 01:01:05.574
parties.

01:01:05.749 --> 01:01:07.968
Most people just use
the calendar app,

01:01:08.142 --> 01:01:10.841
but, you know,
I figure you're not most people.

01:01:12.930 --> 01:01:14.540
You are going, right?

01:01:16.629 --> 01:01:17.456
You have to go.

01:01:17.630 --> 01:01:19.893
I don't have to do anything.

01:01:20.067 --> 01:01:22.548
I mean, true, but...

01:01:22.722 --> 01:01:23.680
you should.

01:01:31.470 --> 01:01:33.646
Okay.

01:01:33.820 --> 01:01:38.172
Look, I know you think
people think you're weird,

01:01:38.346 --> 01:01:42.394
and I'm not gonna lie,
you are.

01:01:42.568 --> 01:01:44.701
But, no, you think being weird
is a bad thing.

01:01:44.875 --> 01:01:48.226
You think you're the only one.
But you know what? You're not.

01:01:48.400 --> 01:01:51.011
There are tons
of other weirdos out there.

01:01:51.185 --> 01:01:55.146
Cool, interesting people
like you.

01:01:55.320 --> 01:01:57.757
You just have to go out
into the world and find them.

01:02:01.935 --> 01:02:04.677
Don't you wanna know
what it's like?

01:02:04.851 --> 01:02:06.853
What you're like
somewhere else?

01:02:09.551 --> 01:02:12.772
[♪♪♪]

01:02:12.946 --> 01:02:15.079
[HEART BEATING]

01:02:15.253 --> 01:02:17.516
UMMA:

01:02:29.963 --> 01:02:31.748
Bye. Good luck.

01:02:41.279 --> 01:02:43.847
[♪♪♪]

01:03:00.907 --> 01:03:01.821
[SIGHS]

01:03:09.611 --> 01:03:10.569
Mom?

01:03:15.400 --> 01:03:16.488
Are you here?

01:03:31.633 --> 01:03:32.634
Hello?

01:03:40.686 --> 01:03:43.558
[♪♪♪]

01:03:48.694 --> 01:03:50.087
Umma?

01:03:57.790 --> 01:03:59.879
[AMANDA HUMMING MUSIC BOX TUNE]

01:04:10.455 --> 01:04:12.413
[WIND WHISTLING]

01:04:13.850 --> 01:04:14.938
Mom?

01:04:22.293 --> 01:04:23.294
[STOPS HUMMING]

01:04:31.389 --> 01:04:32.912
Time to pay our respects.

01:04:33.086 --> 01:04:35.959
[♪♪♪]

01:04:53.367 --> 01:04:54.629
What is all this?

01:04:57.241 --> 01:04:59.460
This is a jesa.

01:04:59.634 --> 01:05:02.289
This is what we do
to honor our ancestors.

01:05:02.463 --> 01:05:06.337
To be with them, so they're
not alone in the afterlife.

01:05:06.511 --> 01:05:08.774
Get down on your knees
and pay your respects.

01:05:10.689 --> 01:05:12.560
Why?

01:05:12.734 --> 01:05:14.780
You said you don't believe
in this stuff.

01:05:14.954 --> 01:05:16.564
[SQUELCHING]

01:05:16.738 --> 01:05:18.131
Do it.
No.

01:05:18.305 --> 01:05:21.656
You stubborn, disrespectful
little girl.

01:05:21.830 --> 01:05:23.745
You remind me
so much of your mother.

01:05:23.920 --> 01:05:26.139
She tried to run away too.

01:05:26.313 --> 01:05:28.794
Away from the home I gave her.

01:05:28.968 --> 01:05:32.798
Do you know what I had to do
when she disobeyed me?

01:05:32.972 --> 01:05:34.539
I had to lock her in a closet

01:05:34.713 --> 01:05:36.845
so she could think about
all the ways she hurt me.

01:05:37.020 --> 01:05:39.805
YOUNG AMANDA:
Umma. Umma.

01:05:39.979 --> 01:05:40.980
[YOUNG AMANDA SCREAMS]

01:05:43.243 --> 01:05:45.028
Mommy, you're scaring me.

01:05:46.594 --> 01:05:49.162
She was scared too,

01:05:49.336 --> 01:05:51.425
because she couldn't see
how much it hurt me

01:05:51.599 --> 01:05:53.471
every time she ran away.

01:05:55.386 --> 01:05:58.345
I needed her to believe me.

01:05:58.519 --> 01:05:59.868
[CRACKLING]She needed to understand

01:06:00.043 --> 01:06:01.914
my pain was real.

01:06:02.088 --> 01:06:05.570
We had an old lamp.
My favorite lamp.

01:06:05.744 --> 01:06:06.875
With a broken wire.

01:06:07.050 --> 01:06:09.313
[BUZZING]

01:06:09.487 --> 01:06:11.228
[YOUNG AMANDA SCREAMS]

01:06:13.665 --> 01:06:15.232
[DISTORTED]
So I made her hold it,

01:06:15.406 --> 01:06:18.104
until my pain became hers,

01:06:18.278 --> 01:06:20.019
and we could feel it together.

01:06:24.937 --> 01:06:27.244
But she never learned
her lesson.

01:06:33.511 --> 01:06:35.904
You can never escape.

01:06:38.211 --> 01:06:40.431
[♪♪♪]

01:06:46.002 --> 01:06:47.090
[GASPS, SCREAMS]

01:06:53.226 --> 01:06:54.836
[GASPING]

01:07:13.377 --> 01:07:15.248
[SHUDDERING]

01:07:31.830 --> 01:07:34.746
[SQUELCHING]

01:07:34.920 --> 01:07:37.444
[GROWLING]

01:07:43.711 --> 01:07:44.669
[SNARLS]

01:07:49.587 --> 01:07:50.153
[SCREECHES]

01:07:59.162 --> 01:08:00.467
AMANDA:
Chrissy.

01:08:00.641 --> 01:08:02.252
Help me.

01:08:06.430 --> 01:08:08.606
[GASPS, THEN GRUNTING]

01:08:08.780 --> 01:08:10.347
UMMA:

01:08:10.521 --> 01:08:12.044
Get off of me.

01:08:21.270 --> 01:08:22.794
Mommy, it's me.

